{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":201,"text":"The theme of my talk today is,"},{"time":1893,"text":"\"Be an artist, right now.\""},{"time":5101,"text":"Most people, when this subject is brought up,"},{"time":8158,"text":"get tense and resist it:"},{"time":10784,"text":"\"Art doesn't feed me, and right now I'm busy."},{"time":13778,"text":"I have to go to school, get a job,"},{"time":16154,"text":"send my kids to lessons ... \""},{"time":18441,"text":"You think, \"I'm too busy. I don't have time for art.\""},{"time":23976,"text":"There are hundreds of reasons why we can't be artists right now."},{"time":27437,"text":"Don't they just pop into your head?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":28992,"text":"There are so many reasons why we can't be,"},{"time":30815,"text":"indeed, we're not sure why we should be."},{"time":33375,"text":"We don't know why we should be artists,"},{"time":35068,"text":"but we have many reasons why we can't be."},{"time":38971,"text":"Why do people instantly resist the idea of associating themselves with art?"},{"time":43346,"text":"Perhaps you think art is for the greatly gifted"},{"time":47214,"text":"or for the thoroughly and professionally trained."},{"time":52266,"text":"And some of you may think you've strayed too far from art."},{"time":56609,"text":"Well you might have, but I don't think so."},{"time":61227,"text":"This is the theme of my talk today."},{"time":63696,"text":"We are all born artists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65498,"text":"If you have kids, you know what I mean."},{"time":68542,"text":"Almost everything kids do is art."},{"time":73427,"text":"They draw with crayons on the wall."},{"time":76005,"text":"They dance to Son Dam Bi's dance on TV,"},{"time":79157,"text":"but you can't even call it Son Dam Bi's dance -- it becomes the kids' own dance."},{"time":83015,"text":"So they dance a strange dance and inflict their singing on everyone."},{"time":88301,"text":"Perhaps their art is something only their parents can bear,"},{"time":92275,"text":"and because they practice such art all day long,"},{"time":97472,"text":"people honestly get a little tired around kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100751,"text":"Kids will sometimes perform monodramas --"},{"time":103906,"text":"playing house is indeed a monodrama or a play."},{"time":107452,"text":"And some kids, when they get a bit older,"},{"time":110131,"text":"start to lie."},{"time":112151,"text":"Usually parents remember the very first time their kid lies."},{"time":117242,"text":"They're shocked."},{"time":118587,"text":"\"Now you're showing your true colors,\" Mom says. She thinks, \"Why does he take after his dad?\""},{"time":122155,"text":"She questions him, \"What kind of a person are you going to be?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":125361,"text":"But you shouldn't worry."},{"time":126932,"text":"The moment kids start to lie is the moment storytelling begins."},{"time":133152,"text":"They are talking about things they didn't see."},{"time":135340,"text":"It's amazing. It's a wonderful moment."},{"time":137131,"text":"Parents should celebrate."},{"time":139198,"text":"\"Hurray! My boy finally started to lie!\""},{"time":143355,"text":"All right! It calls for celebration."},{"time":145584,"text":"For example, a kid says, \"Mom, guess what? I met an alien on my way home.\""},{"time":148973,"text":"Then a typical mom responds, \"Stop that nonsense.\""},{"time":153424,"text":"Now, an ideal parent is someone who responds like this:"},{"time":157040,"text":"\"Really? An alien, huh? What did it look like? Did it say anything?"},{"time":160112,"text":"Where did you meet it?\" \"Um, in front of the supermarket.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":161816,"text":"When you have a conversation like this,"},{"time":164138,"text":"the kid has to come up with the next thing to say to be responsible for what he started."},{"time":170513,"text":"Soon, a story develops."},{"time":172677,"text":"Of course this is an infantile story,"},{"time":177154,"text":"but thinking up one sentence after the next"},{"time":180970,"text":"is the same thing a professional writer like me does."},{"time":185038,"text":"In essence, they are not different."},{"time":187417,"text":"Roland Barthes once said of Flaubert's novels,"},{"time":190103,"text":"\"Flaubert did not write a novel."},{"time":192709,"text":"He merely connected one sentence after another."},{"time":195714,"text":"The eros between sentences, that is the essence of Flaubert's novel.\""},{"time":200441,"text":"That's right -- a novel, basically, is writing one sentence,"},{"time":203224,"text":"then, without violating the scope of the first one,"},{"time":206683,"text":"writing the next sentence."},{"time":208388,"text":"And you continue to make connections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209897,"text":"Take a look at this sentence:"},{"time":211963,"text":"\"One morning, as Gregor Samsa was waking up from anxious dreams, he discovered that in his bed he had been changed into a monstrous verminous bug.\""},{"time":214430,"text":"Yes, it's the first sentence of Franz Kafka's \"The Metamorphosis.\""},{"time":216876,"text":"Writing such an unjustifiable sentence"},{"time":220044,"text":"and continuing in order to justify it,"},{"time":222492,"text":"Kafka's work became the masterpiece of contemporary literature."},{"time":226921,"text":"Kafka did not show his work to his father."},{"time":229670,"text":"He was not on good terms with his father."},{"time":231994,"text":"On his own, he wrote these sentences."},{"time":235790,"text":"Had he shown his father, \"My boy has finally lost it,\" he would've thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239053,"text":"And that's right. Art is about going a little nuts"},{"time":240965,"text":"and justifying the next sentence,"},{"time":243212,"text":"which is not much different from what a kid does."},{"time":246473,"text":"A kid who has just started to lie"},{"time":248004,"text":"is taking the first step as a storyteller."},{"time":251130,"text":"Kids do art."},{"time":253691,"text":"They don't get tired and they have fun doing it."},{"time":255116,"text":"I was in Jeju Island a few days ago."},{"time":256877,"text":"When kids are on the beach, most of them love playing in the water."},{"time":261989,"text":"But some of them spend a lot of time in the sand,"},{"time":264896,"text":"making mountains and seas -- well, not seas,"},{"time":267140,"text":"but different things -- people and dogs, etc."},{"time":271087,"text":"But parents tell them,"},{"time":272500,"text":"\"It will all be washed away by the waves.\""},{"time":274263,"text":"In other words, it's useless."},{"time":276085,"text":"There's no need."},{"time":277229,"text":"But kids don't mind."},{"time":279095,"text":"They have fun in the moment"},{"time":280266,"text":"and they keep playing in the sand."},{"time":282432,"text":"Kids don't do it because someone told them to."},{"time":284698,"text":"They aren't told by their boss"},{"time":286294,"text":"or anyone, they just do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289219,"text":"When you were little, I bet you spent time enjoying the pleasure of primitive art."},{"time":294615,"text":"When I ask my students to write about their happiest moment,"},{"time":298977,"text":"many write about an early artistic experience they had as a kid."},{"time":304901,"text":"Learning to play piano for the first time and playing four hands with a friend,"},{"time":307656,"text":"or performing a ridiculous skit with friends looking like idiots -- things like that."},{"time":312672,"text":"Or the moment you developed the first film you shot with an old camera."},{"time":316023,"text":"They talk about these kinds of experiences."},{"time":318346,"text":"You must have had such a moment."},{"time":320611,"text":"In that moment, art makes you happy"},{"time":322544,"text":"because it's not work."},{"time":324221,"text":"Work doesn't make you happy, does it? Mostly it's tough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326754,"text":"The French writer Michel Tournier has a famous saying."},{"time":329855,"text":"It's a bit mischievous, actually."},{"time":331545,"text":"\"Work is against human nature. The proof is that it makes us tired.\""},{"time":336517,"text":"Right? Why would work tire us if it's in our nature?"},{"time":338002,"text":"Playing doesn't tire us."},{"time":339663,"text":"We can play all night long."},{"time":341098,"text":"If we work overnight, we should be paid for overtime."},{"time":343531,"text":"Why? Because it's tiring and we feel fatigue."},{"time":346815,"text":"But kids, usually they do art for fun. It's playing."},{"time":351497,"text":"They don't draw to sell the work to a client"},{"time":354231,"text":"or play the piano to earn money for the family."},{"time":357256,"text":"Of course, there were kids who had to."},{"time":360032,"text":"You know this gentleman, right?"},{"time":361334,"text":"He had to tour around Europe to support his family --"},{"time":365420,"text":"Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart --"},{"time":367310,"text":"but that was centuries ago, so we can make him an exception."},{"time":370273,"text":"Unfortunately, at some point our art -- such a joyful pastime -- ends."},{"time":374138,"text":"Kids have to go to lessons, to school, do homework"},{"time":377528,"text":"and of course they take piano or ballet lessons,"},{"time":381046,"text":"but they aren't fun anymore."},{"time":382815,"text":"You're told to do it and there's competition. How can it be fun?"},{"time":386147,"text":"If you're in elementary school and you still draw on the wall,"},{"time":391739,"text":"you'll surely get in trouble with your mom."},{"time":395654,"text":"Besides,"},{"time":399521,"text":"if you continue to act like an artist as you get older,"},{"time":402101,"text":"you'll increasingly feel pressure --"},{"time":405769,"text":"people will question your actions and ask you to act properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411824,"text":"Here's my story: I was an eighth grader and I entered a drawing contest at school in Gyeongbokgung."},{"time":418011,"text":"I was trying my best, and my teacher came around"},{"time":420918,"text":"and asked me, \"What are you doing?\""},{"time":424506,"text":"\"I'm drawing diligently,\" I said."},{"time":426320,"text":"\"Why are you using only black?\""},{"time":428223,"text":"Indeed, I was eagerly coloring the sketchbook in black."},{"time":430603,"text":"And I explained,"},{"time":433672,"text":"\"It's a dark night and a crow is perching on a branch.\""},{"time":436919,"text":"Then my teacher said,"},{"time":437917,"text":"\"Really? Well, Young-ha, you may not be good at drawing but you have a talent for storytelling.\""},{"time":443239,"text":"Or so I wished."},{"time":445974,"text":"\"Now you'll get it, you rascal!\" was the response. (Laughter)"},{"time":448742,"text":"\"You'll get it!\" he said."},{"time":450346,"text":"You were supposed to draw the palace, the Gyeonghoeru, etc.,"},{"time":453028,"text":"but I was coloring everything in black,"},{"time":455463,"text":"so he dragged me out of the group."},{"time":457147,"text":"There were a lot of girls there as well,"},{"time":459167,"text":"so I was utterly mortified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460718,"text":"None of my explanations or excuses were heard,"},{"time":465170,"text":"and I really got it big time."},{"time":468383,"text":"If he was an ideal teacher, he would have responded like I said before,"},{"time":472901,"text":"\"Young-ha may not have a talent for drawing,"},{"time":475214,"text":"but he has a gift for making up stories,\" and he would have encouraged me."},{"time":478589,"text":"But such a teacher is seldom found."},{"time":482041,"text":"Later, I grew up and went to Europe's galleries --"},{"time":485004,"text":"I was a university student -- and I thought this was really unfair."},{"time":486905,"text":"Look what I found. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":492303,"text":"Works like this were hung in Basel while I was punished"},{"time":496628,"text":"and stood in front of the palace with my drawing in my mouth."},{"time":502021,"text":"Look at this. Doesn't it look just like wallpaper?"},{"time":505027,"text":"Contemporary art, I later discovered, isn't explained by a lame story like mine."},{"time":506943,"text":"No crows are brought up."},{"time":510888,"text":"Most of the works have no title, Untitled."},{"time":514221,"text":"Anyways, contemporary art in the 20th century"},{"time":517322,"text":"is about doing something weird and filling the void with explanation and interpretation --"},{"time":522691,"text":"essentially the same as I did."},{"time":524170,"text":"Of course, my work was very amateur,"},{"time":526918,"text":"but let's turn to more famous examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530207,"text":"This is Picasso's."},{"time":532808,"text":"He stuck handlebars into a bike seat and called it \"Bull's Head.\" Sounds convincing, right?"},{"time":538609,"text":"Next, a urinal was placed on its side and called \"Fountain\"."},{"time":543253,"text":"That was Duchamp."},{"time":544847,"text":"So filling the gap between explanation and a weird act with stories --"},{"time":549297,"text":"that's indeed what contemporary art is all about."},{"time":553424,"text":"Picasso even made the statement,"},{"time":554812,"text":"\"I draw not what I see but what I think.\""},{"time":558989,"text":"Yes, it means I didn't have to draw Gyeonghoeru."},{"time":561506,"text":"I wish I knew what Picasso said back then. I could have argued better with my teacher."},{"time":565577,"text":"Unfortunately, the little artists within us"},{"time":569379,"text":"are choked to death before we get to fight against the oppressors of art."},{"time":574866,"text":"They get locked in."},{"time":576471,"text":"That's our tragedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577554,"text":"So what happens when little artists get locked in, banished or even killed?"},{"time":582814,"text":"Our artistic desire doesn't go away."},{"time":584197,"text":"We want to express, to reveal ourselves,"},{"time":587294,"text":"but with the artist dead, the artistic desire reveals itself in dark form."},{"time":592532,"text":"In karaoke bars, there are always people who sing"},{"time":595499,"text":"\"She's Gone\" or \"Hotel California,\""},{"time":598041,"text":"miming the guitar riffs."},{"time":600361,"text":"Usually they sound awful. Awful indeed."},{"time":602603,"text":"Some people turn into rockers like this."},{"time":605082,"text":"Or some people dance in clubs."},{"time":607155,"text":"People who would have enjoyed telling stories"},{"time":610557,"text":"end up trolling on the Internet all night long."},{"time":613567,"text":"That's how a writing talent reveals itself on the dark side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616962,"text":"Sometimes we see dads get more excited than their kids"},{"time":620915,"text":"playing with Legos or putting together plastic robots."},{"time":623900,"text":"They go, \"Don't touch it. Daddy will do it for you.\""},{"time":625633,"text":"The kid has already lost interest and is doing something else,"},{"time":627268,"text":"but the dad alone builds castles."},{"time":631277,"text":"This shows the artistic impulses inside us are suppressed, not gone."},{"time":635755,"text":"But they can often reveal themselves negatively, in the form of jealousy."},{"time":639547,"text":"You know the song \"I would love to be on TV\"? Why would we love it?"},{"time":644841,"text":"TV is full of people who do what we wished to do,"},{"time":648669,"text":"but never got to."},{"time":650609,"text":"They dance, they act -- and the more they do, they are praised."},{"time":656738,"text":"So we start to envy them."},{"time":659888,"text":"We become dictators with a remote and start to criticize the people on TV."},{"time":663982,"text":"\"He just can't act.\" \"You call that singing? She can't hit the notes.\""},{"time":669835,"text":"We easily say these sorts of things."},{"time":672125,"text":"We get jealous, not because we're evil,"},{"time":675068,"text":"but because we have little artists pent up inside us."},{"time":679605,"text":"That's what I think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683191,"text":"What should we do then?"},{"time":685029,"text":"Yes, that's right."},{"time":685806,"text":"Right now, we need to start our own art."},{"time":689000,"text":"Right this minute, we can turn off TV,"},{"time":690009,"text":"log off the Internet,"},{"time":692458,"text":"get up and start to do something."},{"time":695158,"text":"Where I teach students in drama school,"},{"time":696893,"text":"there's a course called Dramatics."},{"time":699627,"text":"In this course, all students must put on a play."},{"time":703817,"text":"However, acting majors are not supposed to act."},{"time":707929,"text":"They can write the play, for example,"},{"time":709949,"text":"and the writers may work on stage art."},{"time":712673,"text":"Likewise, stage art majors may become actors, and in this way you put on a show."},{"time":714984,"text":"Students at first wonder whether they can actually do it,"},{"time":718732,"text":"but later they have so much fun. I rarely see anyone who is miserable doing a play."},{"time":723295,"text":"In school, the military or even in a mental institution, once you make people do it, they enjoy it."},{"time":727457,"text":"I saw this happen in the army -- many people had fun doing plays."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732353,"text":"I have another experience:"},{"time":735285,"text":"In my writing class, I give students a special assignment."},{"time":738919,"text":"I have students like you in the class -- many who don't major in writing."},{"time":744819,"text":"Some major in art or music and think they can't write."},{"time":749396,"text":"So I give them blank sheets of paper and a theme."},{"time":753123,"text":"It can be a simple theme:"},{"time":754737,"text":"Write about the most unfortunate experience in your childhood."},{"time":757251,"text":"There's one condition: You must write like crazy. Like crazy!"},{"time":761164,"text":"I walk around and encourage them,"},{"time":763897,"text":"\"Come on, come on!\" They have to write like crazy for an hour or two."},{"time":767641,"text":"They only get to think for the first five minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770849,"text":"The reason I make them write like crazy is because"},{"time":774071,"text":"when you write slowly and lots of thoughts cross your mind,"},{"time":776829,"text":"the artistic devil creeps in."},{"time":779276,"text":"This devil will tell you hundreds of reasons"},{"time":783308,"text":"why you can't write:"},{"time":786238,"text":"\"People will laugh at you. This is not good writing!"},{"time":789073,"text":"What kind of sentence is this? Look at your handwriting!\""},{"time":790623,"text":"It will say a lot of things."},{"time":792200,"text":"You have to run fast so the devil can't catch up."},{"time":794704,"text":"The really good writing I've seen in my class"},{"time":798776,"text":"was not from the assignments with a long deadline,"},{"time":801449,"text":"but from the 40- to 60-minute crazy writing students did"},{"time":804933,"text":"in front of me with a pencil."},{"time":808335,"text":"The students go into a kind of trance."},{"time":810174,"text":"After 30 or 40 minutes, they write without knowing what they're writing."},{"time":814636,"text":"And in this moment, the nagging devil disappears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817601,"text":"So I can say this:"},{"time":819310,"text":"It's not the hundreds of reasons why one can't be an artist,"},{"time":823325,"text":"but rather, the one reason one must be that makes us artists."},{"time":827575,"text":"Why we cannot be something is not important."},{"time":829284,"text":"Most artists became artists because of the one reason."},{"time":832434,"text":"When we put the devil in our heart to sleep and start our own art,"},{"time":836104,"text":"enemies appear on the outside."},{"time":838438,"text":"Mostly, they have the faces of our parents. (Laughter)"},{"time":841294,"text":"Sometimes they look like our spouses,"},{"time":844395,"text":"but they are not your parents or spouses."},{"time":846163,"text":"They are devils. Devils."},{"time":849057,"text":"They came to Earth briefly transformed"},{"time":851001,"text":"to stop you from being artistic, from becoming artists."},{"time":854947,"text":"And they have a magic question."},{"time":856869,"text":"When we say, \"I think I'll try acting. There's a drama school in the community center,\" or"},{"time":863027,"text":"\"I'd like to learn Italian songs,\" they ask, \"Oh, yeah? A play? What for?\""},{"time":867504,"text":"The magic question is, \"What for?\""},{"time":871166,"text":"But art is not for anything."},{"time":874878,"text":"Art is the ultimate goal."},{"time":877132,"text":"It saves our souls and makes us live happily."},{"time":881272,"text":"It helps us express ourselves and be happy without the help of alcohol or drugs."},{"time":886778,"text":"So in response to such a pragmatic question,"},{"time":891118,"text":"we need to be bold."},{"time":893537,"text":"\"Well, just for the fun of it. Sorry for having fun without you,\""},{"time":897981,"text":"is what you should say. \"I'll just go ahead and do it anyway.\""},{"time":902006,"text":"The ideal future I imagine is where we all have multiple identities,"},{"time":907106,"text":"at least one of which is an artist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910887,"text":"Once I was in New York and got in a cab. I took the backseat,"},{"time":914056,"text":"and in front of me I saw something related to a play."},{"time":918213,"text":"So I asked the driver, \"What is this?\""},{"time":919350,"text":"He said it was his profile. \"Then what are you?\" I asked. \"An actor,\" he said."},{"time":923395,"text":"He was a cabby and an actor. I asked, \"What roles do you usually play?\""},{"time":926818,"text":"He proudly said he played King Lear."},{"time":928844,"text":"King Lear."},{"time":930289,"text":"\"Who is it that can tell me who I am?\" -- a great line from King Lear."},{"time":931915,"text":"That's the world I dream of."},{"time":935306,"text":"Someone is a golfer by day and writer by night."},{"time":939241,"text":"Or a cabby and an actor, a banker and a painter,"},{"time":941760,"text":"secretly or publicly performing their own arts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947336,"text":"In 1990, Martha Graham, the legend of modern dance, came to Korea."},{"time":952207,"text":"The great artist, then in her 90s, arrived at Gimpo Airport"},{"time":957979,"text":"and a reporter asked her a typical question:"},{"time":961044,"text":"\"What do you have to do to become a great dancer?"},{"time":963651,"text":"Any advice for aspiring Korean dancers?\""},{"time":966231,"text":"Now, she was the master. This photo was taken in 1948 and she was already a celebrated artist."},{"time":971226,"text":"In 1990, she was asked this question."},{"time":973417,"text":"And here's what she answered:"},{"time":976101,"text":"\"Just do it.\""},{"time":980018,"text":"Wow. I was touched."},{"time":981536,"text":"Only those three words and she left the airport. That's it."},{"time":985628,"text":"So what should we do now?"},{"time":988859,"text":"Let's be artists, right now. Right away. How?"},{"time":992585,"text":"Just do it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":993577,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995191,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}